Add the following JavaScript code inside the <script> tags:
javascript
Copy code
$(document).ready(function() {
  $(".testimonial .tabs li").click(function() {
    var index = $(this).index();
    $(this).addClass('active').siblings().removeClass('active');
    $(".testimonial .carousel-item").eq(index).addClass('active').siblings().removeClass('active');
  });
});
Update the CSS classes to include the active state styles. Add the following CSS code inside the <style> tags:
css
Copy code
body .testimonial .row .tabs li.active::before,
body .testimonial .row .tabs li.active::after,
body .testimonial .row .tabs li:focus {
  /* Add your active state styles here */
  border: 10px solid red;
}
body .testimonial .row .carousel-inner .carousel-item.active {
  /* Add your active state styles here */
  display: block;
}
With these changes, the tabs should be functional, and clicking on a tab will switch the corresponding testimonial slide.

